<P>Before I went to Bed, they let me know<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="OXF" EXTENT="1 letter"> that there was to be a Meeting at <HI>Wiccomb</HI> nex<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="OXF" EXTENT="1 letter"> Day; and that &s;ome of the Family would g<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="OXF" EXTENT="1 letter"> to it. I was very glad of it: for I greatly d<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="OXF" EXTENT="1 letter">+&s;ired to go to Meetings; and this fell very ap<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="OXF" EXTENT="1 letter">+ly, it being in my way home. Next Mornin<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="OXF" EXTENT="1 letter"> <HI>I&s;aac Penington</HI> him&s;elf went, having <HI>Anne Cu<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="OXF" EXTENT="1 letter">+tis</HI> with him: and I accompanied them.</P>
