<P>I governed my &s;elf, in a free, yet re&s;pect|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="OXF" EXTENT="1 letter">ul Carriage towards her, that I thereby both <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="OXF" EXTENT="1 letter">re&s;erved a fair Reputation with my Friends, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="OXF" EXTENT="1 letter">nd Enjoyed as much of her Favour and Kind|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="OXF" EXTENT="1 letter">e&s;s, in a virtuous and firm Friend&s;hip, as was fit for her to &s;hew, or for me to &s;eek.</P>
<P>Thus leading a quiet and contented Life, I <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="OXF" EXTENT="1 letter">ad Lei&s;ure &s;ometimes to write a Copy of Ver|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="OXF" EXTENT="1 letter">s, on one Occa&s;ion or another, as the <HI>Poetick Vein</HI> naturally opened, without taking Pains to <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="OXF" EXTENT="1 letter">oli&s;h them. Such was this which follows; <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="OXF" EXTENT="1 letter">cca&s;ioned by the &s;uddain Death of &s;ome lu&s;ty People in their full Strength.</P>
<LG>
