<P><MILESTONE N="1675" UNIT="date"> He lived not long after this; but the Impre<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="OXF" EXTENT="1 letter">+&s;ion his crafty fal&s;e and frothy Carriage (as we<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="OXF" EXTENT="1 letter"> at this time, as before) had made upon m<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="OXF" EXTENT="1 letter"> Mind, drew from me, when I heard of h<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="OXF" EXTENT="1+ letters"> Death, &s;omething like an <HI>Epitaph,</HI> in a drollin<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="OXF" EXTENT="1 letter"> Stile, as him&s;elf was wont to U&s;e. And th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="OXF" EXTENT="1+ letters"> it was.</P>
