<HEAD>A Li&s;t of the MANUSCRIPTS he left behind him.</HEAD>
<LIST>
<ITEM>1. <HI>AN An&s;wer to a Paper directed to the Members of the Society of</HI> Quakers, <HI>e&s;pecially to tho&s;e that frequent the Town of</HI> Fever&s;ham (<HI>in</HI> Kent) 1672. To which the Prie&s;t replying, <HI>T. Ellwood</HI> writ a <HI>Rejoinder,</HI> very notable, and worth the Publi&s;hing. The whole about 15 Sheets, in 1672, or 1673.</ITEM>
